comments: Moore (NOP) makes marginal contact to Booker's (PHX) arm during the drive that does not affect his ability to maintain control of the ball and make the pass.
During the rebound, Booker (PHX) jumps into and dislodges Redick (NOP) from his position as Redick attempts to retrieve the rebound.
Bridges (PHX) makes contact to Ingram's (NOP) arm during his shooting motion that affects his driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) splits his feet.
Holiday (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position on Booker (PHX) during the drive before Booker makes the errant pass.
During the pick, Bridges (PHX) and Redick (NOP) engage and disengage.

T. Johnson (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position and cleanly dislodges the ball during the driving shot attempt by Ingram (NOP).  After the dislodge, any follow-through contact to Ingram's arm is deemed incidental.
During the inbound, C. Johnson (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position on Moore (NOP) and cleanly dislodges the ball.
Williams (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position on T. Johnson (PHX) during the drive.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Bridges (PHX) is the last player on the floor to make contact with the ball prior to the out of bounds.
Bridges (PHX) maintains a legal guarding position on Holiday (NOP) and cleanly dislodges the ball.
Holiday (NOP) cleanly dislodges the ball from Booker (PHX) and any body contact following the dislodge is deemed incidental.
Redick (NOP) steps out of bounds into the inbounder's space while defending the inbounds play.
Moore (NOP) places a resting hand on C. Johnson's (PHX) opposite-side hip as he cuts to the basket but the contact does not affect his FOM.
Moore (NOP) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by C. Johnson (PHX).
Booker (PHX) makes slight contact to Holiday's (NOP) arm but it does not affect his SQBR.
C. Johnson (PHX) makes marginal contact to Redick's (NOP) arm but the contact does not disrupt his dribble.
T. Johnson (PHX) cleanly deflects the pass that is intended for Ingram (NOP) and the contact following the dislodge is considered incidental.
Holiday (NOP) makes incidental "high-five" contact with C. Johnson (PHX) that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
During the rebound, T. Johnson (PHX) makes marginal contact to Redick (NOP).  As a result of the contact, Redick's momentum creates incidental contact with Oubre Jr. (PHX).
T. Johnson (PHX) commits a take foul on Holiday (NOP).  The initial contact by T. Johnson causes Holiday to move his pivot foot before the whistle for the take foul is correctly called.
Booker (PHX) and Holiday (NOP) engage and disengage during the inbound play.
